</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136ACE7327FFAD91D4FDD5F761FDAB" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB639457327FFAD91D4FDD5F761FDAB" blockId="10.[191,1440,533,593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD91D4FDD5F733FDD5" bold="true" box="[192,324,533,559]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD9335FDD5F577FDD5" authorityName="Botero and Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[545,768,533,559]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavoquadripunctata">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD9335FDD5F577FDD5" box="[545,768,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">flavoquadripunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the four yellowish-brown maculae present on each elytron.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136ACE7327FFAD91D4FDA1F479FB62" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB639457327FFAD91D4FDA1F555FBA8" blockId="10.[191,1442,608,1107]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD91D4FDA1F758FD81" bold="true" box="[192,303,609,635]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD9020FDA1F4E2FD80" authority="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="Botero &amp; Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[308,661,608,634]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavoquadripunctata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD9020FDA1F4E2FD80" box="[308,661,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD938EFDA1F556FD80" bold="true" box="[666,801,608,635]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E582C7327FFAD938EFDA1F556FD80" box="[666,801,608,635]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD928DFDA1F2BEFD81" authority="Martins, 1970" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1970" box="[921,1225,608,635]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysthymia">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD928DFDA1F5DAFD80" box="[921,941,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD92ADFDA0F25DFD80" box="[953,1066,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">dysthymia</emphasis>
Martins, 1970
</taxonomicName>
by the anterior half of the elytra with two yellowish-brown maculae, and presence of yellowish-brown maculae on posterior half of the elytra. Although 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD90BCFD65F44EFD44" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1970" box="[424,569,676,702]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysthymia">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD90BCFD65F7CCFD44" box="[424,443,677,702]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD90DCFD64F44EFD44" box="[456,569,676,702]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">dysthymia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains formally known only by females (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9503FD64F2F8FD44" box="[1047,1167,676,702]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 19–22</figureCitation>
; see also photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="54B287E77327FFAD91FFFD05F73AFD25" box="[235,333,709,735]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
on 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844B47327FFAD906EFD05F46FFD1A" author="Bezark LG" box="[378,536,709,736]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref14160" refString="Bezark LG. 2022. A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the World. New World Cerambycidae Catalog. Available at http: // bezbycids. com / byciddb / wdefault. asp? w = n / (Last accessed 13 January 2022.)" type="url" year="2022">Bezark (2022)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844B47327FFAD9345FD06F490FD1A" author="CNC &amp; Canadian National Collection" box="[593,743,710,736]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" refId="ref14436" refString="CNC (Canadian National Collection). 2020. Taxon search. Available at https: // www. cnc. agr. gc. ca / taxonomy / TaxonSearch. php / (Last accessed 13 January 2022.)" type="url" year="2020">CNC (2020))</bibRefCitation>
, the new species cannot be the male of this species due to the following differences (this type of sexual dimorphism is not present in the other species of the genus): pronotum with distinctly glabrous longitudinal areas; anterolateral tubercles of the pronotum almost absent (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9456FCC9F3E5FCD9" box="[1346,1426,777,803]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); anterocentral region of the pronotum without tubercle; in lateral view, pronotum not arched (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD95E6FCEBF333FCBF" box="[1266,1348,811,837]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
); elytral punctures sparser (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9081FC8CF792FC9C" box="[405,485,844,870]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); elytral pubescence denser and forming longitudinal bands (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9587FC8CF294FC9C" box="[1171,1251,844,870]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); and elytra with two yellowish-brown maculae on posterior half of the elytra (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9249FCAEF5DCFC72" box="[861,939,878,904]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD92CCFCAFF21DFC72" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1970" box="[984,1130,878,905]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysthymia">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD92CCFCAFF59BFC72" box="[984,1004,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD92EDFCAEF21DFC72" box="[1017,1130,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">dysthymia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the pronotum has a narrow glabrous longitudinal area only centrally (almost absent in the 
<typeStatus id="54B287E77327FFAD9293FC50F59AFC51" box="[903,1005,912,939]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
), anterolateral angles of the pronotum elevated and conical (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD90BBFC71F452FC36" box="[431,549,945,972]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 20, 22</figureCitation>
), anterocentral region of the pronotum with distinct carina-shaped tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9462FC71F773FC17" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 20, 22</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, pronotum arched (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD939EFC13F4AFFC17" box="[650,728,979,1005]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), elytral punctures distinctly denser (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9565FC13F2C8FC17" box="[1137,1215,979,1005]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); elytral pubescence sparser and not forming longitudinal bands (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD93ADFC35F57EFBF5" box="[697,777,1013,1039]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), and the elytra with one large yellowish-brown macula on posterior half (
<figureCitation id="133225C07327FFAD9073FBD6F7C0FBCB" box="[359,439,1046,1073]" captionStart="Figures 14–22" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1344,213,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–22. Neocompsa spp. 14–18) Neocompsa flavoquadripunctata Botero and Santos-Silva, sp. nov., holotype male: 14) Dorsal habitus; 15) Ventral habitus; 16) Lateral habitus; 17) Head, frontal view; 18) Prothorax, lateral view.19–22) Neocompsa dysthymia Martins, 1970, female from Mexico (Nuevo Leon): 19) Dorsal habitus; 20) Head, frontal view; 21) Prothorax, lateral view; 22) Pronotal tubercles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). García-Morales et al. (2014) reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD9267FBD7F273FBCA" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1970" box="[883,1028,1046,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Neocompsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dysthymia">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD9267FBD7F5F1FBCA" box="[883,902,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD9287FBD6F273FBCA" box="[915,1028,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">dysthymia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Mexican state of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF7A77327FFAD940EFBD6F3EAFBCA" box="[1306,1437,1046,1072]" country="Mexico" name="Tamaulipas" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Tamaulipas</collectingRegion>
. However, the sex of the specimens was not mentioned.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB639457327FFAD91D4FBBBF479FB62" blockId="10.[192,526,1147,1176]" box="[192,526,1147,1176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C67327FFAD91D4FBBBF479FB62" authority="Lacordaire, 1868" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1868" box="[192,526,1147,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oemini">
<emphasis id="B97DE5577327FFAD91D4FBBBF479FB62" bold="true" box="[192,526,1147,1176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">OEMINI Lacordaire, 1868</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
